definitions.820-00165: What is 820-00165? a LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER.
definitions.U5110: What is U5110? This chip is responsible for SMC_RESET_L in many Macbook models..

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> wont boot
threads.message:
Arrived with liquid damage and the fan spinning fast the second it was powered on.

<CHIP>U8130</CHIP> and <RESISTOR>R8133</RESISTOR> were replaced along with <CHIP>U5110</CHIP> and <RESISTOR>R5125</RESISTOR>. After replacement no change still fast fan second it was powered on with no light.

After replacing the SMC, fan spins normal now light is back but turns off after a few seconds, then turns back on with no usb activity or chime. During the first fan spin draws around 336 ma. When it turns back on draws the normal amperage is drawn around 550-600ma

Tried known good bios with no change.

Sound like bad CPU from <CHIP>U8130</CHIP> and <RESISTOR>R8133</RESISTOR> being hit with liquid? If not what should be checked next??

Also heated CPU with good flux

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> wont boot
threads.message:
Check all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces.
Clean/remove J6100.

threads.title: <LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER>820-00165</LOGIC BOARD PART NUMBER> wont boot
threads.message:
all SPI Bus Series Termination resistors and traces  are good

J6100 removed

no change
